{"type":"message","id":"ba2b86d3","parentId":"99c6996d","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:34:18.074Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 21:34 GMT+2] OPERATION: DIRECT BROADCAST & RAW TRUTH.\n\n1.  **Broadcaster Script (`scripts/broadcast_log.py`):**\n    *   Create script using `requests`.\n    *   *Input:* `filepath`.\n    *   *Logic:* Read file -> Split into 3500-char chunks -> Loop send via Telegram API (`sendMessage`).\n    *   *Header:* \"[BROADCAST START] File: {filename}\"\n    *   *Footer:* \"[BROADCAST END]\"\n\n2.  **Raw Extraction (`reports/ALL_ISSUES_RAW.md`):**\n    *   *Source:* `logs/performance_audit.log`, `logs/bot_*.log`.\n    *   *Filter:* `grep -E \"ERROR|WARN|TIMEOUT|CRITICAL|Traceback\"` (No summarization!).\n    *   *Write:* `reports/ALL_ISSUES_RAW.md`.\n\n3.  **Execute Broadcast:**\n    *   Run `python scripts/broadcast_log.py reports/ALL_ISSUES_RAW.md` (Inject Token).\n\n4.  **Agent Report:**\n    *   \"Broadcaster Active. Stand by.\""}],"timestamp":1771356858071}}
{"type":"message","id":"447e5516","parentId":"ba2b86d3","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:34:33.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Initiating Broadcast Logic**\n\nI'm currently focused on the initial phase. My immediate task is to conceptualize the Python script's structure. I'm prioritizing efficient file reading and chunking. Telegram API integration is next, with a focus on error handling and message delivery confirmation.\n\n\n**Outlining Script Functionality**\n\nI've sketched out the `broadcast_log.py` script's main sections. File reading will use buffered I/O for speed. Telegram integration will need robust error detection for handling API limits and failures. The raw log extraction process, using `grep`, is now the main task. I'm focusing on crafting the correct patterns for each log file.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771356872950_132","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport sys\nimport requests\nimport time\n\ndef broadcast_file(filepath, bot_token, chat_id):\n    \"\"\"Reads a file and broadcasts it to Telegram in chunks.\"\"\"\n    \n    if not os.path.exists(filepath):\n        print(f\"Error: File not found: {filepath}\")\n        return\n\n    filename = os.path.basename(filepath)\n    header = f\"[BROADCAST START] File: {filename}\"\n    footer = \"[BROADCAST END]\"\n    \n    chunk_size = 3500\n    \n    try:\n        with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error reading file: {e}\")\n        return\n\n    # Send Header\n    send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, header)\n    \n    # Send Chunks\n    if content:\n        for i in range(0, len(content), chunk_size):\n            chunk = content[i:i + chunk_size]\n            send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, chunk)\n            time.sleep(1) # Rate limit protection\n    else:\n         send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, \"(File is empty)\")\n\n    # Send Footer\n    send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, footer)\n\ndef send_telegram_message(bot_token, chat_id, text):\n    url = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{bot_token}/sendMessage\"\n    payload = {\n        \"chat_id\": chat_id,\n        \"text\": text,\n        \"parse_mode\": \"Markdown\" # Optional, might break if raw logs have markdown chars, but requested usually implies plain text. Let's stick to safe text if possible or disable parse_mode if issues arise. Actually, raw logs often contain special chars. Let's NOT use parse_mode to be safe, or just basic. The prompt didn't specify, but raw logs usually break Markdown. I'll omit parse_mode for safety.\n    }\n    # Removing parse_mode to ensure raw logs don't break delivery\n    if \"parse_mode\" in payload:\n        del payload[\"parse_mode\"]\n        \n    try:\n        response = requests.post(url, json=payload)\n        response.raise_for_status()\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Failed to send chunk: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python broadcast_log.py <filepath>\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n        \n    filepath = sys.argv[1]\n    \n    # Retrieve credentials from environment variables (secure injection)\n    bot_token = os.environ.get(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n    chat_id = os.environ.get(\"TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID\")\n    \n    if not bot_token or not chat_id:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN and TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID environment variables must be set.\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    broadcast_file(filepath, bot_token, chat_id)\n","file_path":"scripts/broadcast_log.py"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771356873654_133","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p reports\ngrep -E \"ERROR|WARN|TIMEOUT|CRITICAL|Traceback\" logs/performance_audit.log logs/bot_*.log > reports/ALL_ISSUES_RAW.md\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771356873764_134","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python scripts/broadcast_log.py reports/ALL_ISSUES_RAW.md","env":{"TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID":"5505036725","TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN":"7734896200:AAFnz4nQ-qG-tOouXDKTgn-rO6K7x7XpQv4"}}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"message_1771356873888_135","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"Broadcaster Active. Stand by."}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4631,"output":1045,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5676,"cost":{"input":0.009262,"output":0.01254,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021802000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771356858074}}
